Package org.microbean.type

Class JavaType.Token<T>

java.lang.Object
org.microbean.type.JavaType.Token<T>
Type Parameters:
T - the modeled type; often parameterized
Enclosing class:
JavaType
public abstract static class JavaType.Token<T> extends Object
A holder of a Type that embodies Gafter's gadget.

To use this class, create a new instance of an anonymous subclass of it, and then call type() on it:

 // type will be a ParameterizedType whose rawType is List.class and
 // whose sole type argument is String.class
 Type type = new Token<List<String>>() {}.type();
Author:
Laird Nelson
